model.description: Voltage supplied to the Analogue side of the ADC to power chage collection signals from pixels to the chip. Acceptable range is (1.8 to 1.9V)
model.title: P$pacman: VDDA

model.description: Each pacman should acknowledge reception of a 1Hz sync signal. Missing acknowledgements in particular Pacmen may indicate a problem in those pacmen. If the signal is missing from all Pacmen it may indicate a problem with the sync pulse transmission.
model.title: Sync Pulse

model.description: Highest 100 Data Rates over the last 5m (expressed as # packets per second) by pixel for the chosen tile. Each value is a 10s Mean. Yellow / Red thresholds = 1 / 5 p/s
model.title: P$pacman: Chip Hit Count

panels.description: Green bars are centered at Pixel-level Mean ADC value, the top/bottom of the bars are at Mean +/- RMS. All values are calculated over a 10s window.  Red thresholds are < 5 or > 254. Yellow threshold is 250

panels.description: Histogram shows distribution of Pixel-level ADC mean values over the global time window. The bucket size is 1. ADC values are recorded using 8 bits. All mean values in this histogram are calculated over a 10s window
panels.title: P$pacman: ADC Pixel Distribution (1s Mean)

panels.description: Highest 100 pixel data packet rates (expressed as # packets per second - p/s) within a given pacman. Each value represents the  mean rate recorded over the last 30s. Yellow/Red thresholds = 1/5 p/s

panels.description: The highest 100 ADC mean values recorded over the last 30s. ADC values are recorded using 8 bits. A value of 255 indicates the ADC maxed out, which could mean we're missing information. This could require an expert to reset the threshold.  Yellow / Red thresholds = 250 / 254
panels.title: Top Pixel ADC Values P$pacman

panels.description: Digital voltage supplied to digital side of ADC to power data transfer to and from chips. Acceptable range is (1.6 to 1.7V) for all pacmen except P5-P6 whose acceptable range is (1.15 to 1.25V) - the exception is needed because of differences between versions of the chips used (V2A versus V2B)
panels.title: P$pacman: VDDD

panels.description: Current supplied to digital side of ADC to power data transferred to and from the chip. Acceptable range is (400-700mA)
panels.title: P$pacman: IDDD

panels.description: Current supplied to the analogue side of the ADC to power charge collection from pixel to the chip. Acceptable range for most pacmen (150-475mA), but P5 and P6 are distinct (because of distinct models of chips/pacmen) with thresholds (160-110)
panels.title: P$pacman: IDDA

panels.description: Invalid parity indicates that bits flipped at some point in the packet's transmission from chip to pacman. Invalid Parity % = sum (invalid parity) / sum (total) for each 10s interval over the chosen pacman. Y-axis is log base 2. Yellow threshold is 1%, Red threshold is 10%.
panels.title: P$pacman: Invalid Parity Rate (10s Mean)

panels.description: FIFO > 1/2 (or Full) is the fraction of times the FIFO was more than half full (or Full) divided by the total number of observations over a 10s window. "Shared" FIFO is calculated at the chip level. This graph shows the mean chip level ratio for the entire system. This stacked bar chart shows the FIFO > 1/2 (but not completely full) as a blue bar. On top of the blue bar is FIFO full shown as a red bar. Yellow / Red Thresholds are 0.1 / 0.2
panels.title: P$pacman: Shared FIFO > 1/2 and Full (10s Max)

panels.title: P$pacman: Data Rates by Tile (10s Mean)

panels.description: Each tile has 4 Input-Output (IO) channels through which data is transmitted. For a given pacman each IO_channel is uniquely numbered as labeled in the pie charts below. The pie chart shows the percentage distribution of data through each IO_channel from the last 10s recorded values. The text shows the 10s Mean Data Rates (expressed as packet count per second) and the unique IO_channel number. There are no threshold indications
panels.title: P$pacman: Data Rate IO Channel Distribution by Tile (10s Mean)
P$pacman Long Term Data Rates (1m mean)

panels.description: Mean over 10s of Data Rate (expressed as packets per second, p/s) by pacman. Y-axis is log base 2. Yellow/Red threasholds = 30k/300k packets/s. The Data Rate sent to InfluxDB is sent by IO_channel. To get the Data Rate for the full tile we have to sum all of the 32 IO_channels in a particular pacman. To get the 10s mean we sum all of the IO_channels over a 10 second period and then divide by 10.
